Construction 
To classify all the possible Penrose limits of , we could follow the method of "celestial spheres",
consisting of looking at the orbits of the tangent vectors at a point
under the isometry group, but this requires finding a group
representation of the Killing vectors. Clearly starting from the
metric () the null geodesics of  which are going to give
non-trivial Penrose limit spaces are those for which  varies
with the affine parameter. Otherwise the  dependence of the
metric vanishes in the limit and we get flat Minkowski space. In
particular, the limit along the null geodesic of tangent vector
, ie along  the direction of propagation of the
gravitational wave in the horospheres of (), yields flat space.

